Package main

Class Athlete

java.lang.Object
main.Buyable
main.Athlete
public class Athlete extends Buyable
Represents the athletes that make up a Team. Athletes have various attributes that are used when they compete in Matches. Offense determines the attacking power of the athlete, and goes up against the defence of the enemy team's athletes. Stamina is a third attribute that is deducted at the end of each round, and any athletes who have zero stamina are removed from play. Athletes can also use items to improve their attributes.
Version:
1.11
Author:
mdi48, bsm62

  • Field Details

    • injuryWeeks

      public int injuryWeeks
      Represents the number of weeks since the athlete was last injured. Lower values increase the chance of an athlete quitting, while higher values have no effect. The default value is 10 to distinguish from 0, which is used when an athlete has been injured in the current week.

    • winWeeks

      public int winWeeks
      Represents the number of weeks since the athlete last won a Match. Lower values increase the chance of an athlete gaining bonuses from training, while higher values have no effect. The default value is 10 to distinguish from 0, which is used when an athlete has won a match in the current week.

  • Constructor Details

    • Athlete

      public Athlete()
      Constructs a playable instance of Athlete. These are used to populate Market with athletes that can be bought and used by the player. The athlete's class, name, and attributes are randomly assigned using GenerateStats.

    • Athlete

      public Athlete(String type)
      Constructs a non-playable instance of Athlete, used to populate NPC Teams. The athletes' class must be specified since they are used to fill specific team positions. The name and attributes are randomly assigned using GenerateStats.
      Parameters:
      type - sets the athlete's class

  • Method Details

    • useItem

      public void useItem(Item item)
      Applies effects of an Item to the athlete. This modifies the athletes statistics, and removes one of the Item from the Player's inventor.
      Parameters:
      item - specifics the instance of Item to be used

    • limitValue

      public int limitValue(int value, int max)
      Returns a value if inside a specified range. If the value is inside the range, returns the value unchanged. If the value is greater than the upper bound, returns the upper bound instead If the value is less than the lower bound, returns the lower bound instead. In this case the lower bound is always zero.
      Parameters:
      value - the value to be limited
      max - the upper bound.
      Returns:
      the value or nearest bound
